19 "19-13-51.
20 As used in this article, the term:
21 (1) 'Court' means judges in the classes of courts identified in Title 15, military judges as
22 defined in Code Section 38-2-1001, and any other person while acting as such a judge
23 pursuant to designation as otherwise authorized by law.
24 (2) 'Foreign court' means a court of competent jurisdiction in any state other than this
25 state or any territory or tribal jurisdiction in the United States.
26 (3) 'Foreign protective order' means any temporary order of protection, order of
27 protection, restraining order, injunction, pretrial release order, or sentencing order that
28 prohibits contact, acts of family violence, or stalking issued by a foreign court.
29 (4) 'Law enforcement officer' means any agent or officer of this state, or a political
30 subdivision or municipality thereof, who, as a full-time or part-time employee, is vested
31 either expressly by law or by virtue of public employment or service with authority to
32 enforce the criminal or traffic laws and whose duties include the preservation of public
33 order, the protection of life and property, or the prevention, detection, or investigation of
34 crime. Such term also includes the following: a state or local officer, law enforcement
35 officer of the organized militia as defined in Code Section 38-2-1001, sheriff, deputy
36 sheriff, dispatcher, 9-1-1 operator, police officer, prosecuting attorney, member of the
37 State Board of Pardons and Paroles, a hearing officer of the State Board of Pardons and
38 Paroles, and a community supervision officer of the Department of Community
39 Supervision.
40 (5) 'Modification' means any amendment, dismissal, or continuance.
